added.title: Whose Dimension Is It Anyway?
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part IV: Wren enlists Craig in a trans dimensional dream experiment.

added.title: Dude Where's My Bobby?
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part V: A night of candy brings out Craig and Bobby's inner bad boys.

added.title: The Slumber Party
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part VI: Craig and friends compete in a series of cutthroat games to win Eliza's mystery prize.

added.title: Drown Town Abbey
added.description: Each team has a member placed into a clear glass tank that is locked and slowly filling with water. In order to free them, they must retrieve the codes at the far end of a very dangerous obstacle course.

added.title: Numbskull Island
added.description: It's just a normal game of capture the flag… except the flag is a skull, and your opponents are armed with fire hoses, toilet plunger harpoons and giant rolling boulders… which is nothing like capture the flag.

added.title: Jurassic Fart
added.description: After an all-bean breakfast the teams must cross the island in silence to avoid being eaten by raptors. That's right, this episode has dinosaurs... and lots of farting. The first team to reach the other side claims victory.

added.title: Launch Back of Notre Game
added.description: Catapult your team member into distant scoring zones to earn points but if you miss you'll be landing in a penalty zone filled with all kind of evil. The first team to reach 10,000 points wins. The losing team, as always, will be sending someone home.

added.title: The Wheel of Vomit
added.description: Chef finally gets to show off his fancy culinary skills in an eating challenge where each dish is a tastebud's nightmare. The last camper still eating wins immunity. The rest are all up for elimination.

added.title: Paddle Field Earth
added.description: Today's challenge involves canoeing, hiking and mountain climbing. It's just like normal summer camp!! Except that you canoe over a waterfall, hike through a geyser field and climb a mountain that's actually the world's biggest beehive. It's nothing like summer camp.

added.title: Tortoise Rigamortis
added.description: With just 5 campers remaining things are getting tense. So today is just about having fun taking selfies with wild animals. Everyone had their rabies shot?

added.title: Slay Cheese
added.description: It's picture day at Acme Loo! Babs accidentally shrinks herself, Buster fails to get the perfect photo day haircut, Plucky gives lessons on being direct, and Hamton struggles to find his photo persona.

added.title: Tooned In Space
added.description: The toons take Marvin the Martian's class, and head to space. Buster tries to cheer up a homesick Babs, Plucky searches for a space outfit, and Sweetie is too obsessed with a video game to notice any of it - even when the aliens attack!

added.title: The Prince and the Unruly Royal
added.description: Prince Ivandoe receives instructions from his father, The Mighty Stag. He is to escort his spoilt cousin Dudley to a correctional school, ran by Posy Pippins - the strictest and most feared Governess in the land! However, along the way, much to Bert's dismay, Ivandoe falls under the influence of the unruly Dudley and starts to misbehave. So much so that when they arrive at Posy Pippins' Unruly School, she decides to keep both Dudley and Ivandoe! Bert attempts to rescue Prince Ivandoe by posing as an even stricter Governor.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Show-Off Stallion
added.description: When the legendary Mighty Stallion "out-hero's" Prince Ivandoe by saving the Bunny Village from a terrifying beastie, Ivandoe loses his confidence. Even though the Stallion demands payments in carrots, which is in direct violation of the Hero Code, Ivandoe feels he cannot compete with such a magnificent fellow. Bert must help his master find his mojo again, before the Bunny Village is destroyed by an even bigger terrifying beastie!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Squeak of Obedience
added.description: Feral and her gang of cat-thieves have stolen Prince Ivandoe's map to Eagle Mountain. Cupcake, the pink-poodle survivalist offers to train Prince Ivandoe to become a Jungle Warrior. So that together they can infiltrate Feral's camp and get back whats theirs. For Feral also stole a precious item from Cupcake... one that exerts a strange hold over him - "The Squeak of Obedience!"
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Princenappers
added.description: Whilst travelling through the notoriously dangerous Forest of Outlaws, Prince Ivandoe is repeatedly Princenapped! First by a gang of wolves in disguise, then by Boaris and his Merry Boars, and finally by Feral and her gang of cat-thieves - all of them hoping to secure a royal ransom. Luckily for Prince Ivandoe and Bert, they are rescued by the fair Jezabel - though, as it turns out, not with the noblest of intentions.
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Playdate
added.description: Prince Ivandoe is a prisoner in the castle dungeon of Jezabel's mother, Grizabella - the unpredictable and slightly terrifying "Queen of Thieves". Whilst waiting for a royal random, Grizabella encourages her daughter to enjoy her "playdate" with the little prince. Prince Ivandoe is all too eager to do the same. However, when Grizabella demands that Prince Ivandoe perform as her Royal Jester - Ivandoe and Bert realise they need to escape. At once!!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Floor is Grape Jelly
added.description: When David is frustrated to be called home early to help with his baby sister, Barney creates a magical game where David is reminded how good it feels to help others. He leaves the park excited to help out as a big brother.

added.title: I Lovey You
added.description: Barney's magic creates a nighttime adventure in the park, but David is scared of the dark. Barney becomes a giant glowing action figure to help David calm down so he can stay and play with his friends.

added.title: Mel's Greatest Treasure
added.description: Mel is on a quest to find a special treasure and accidentally makes a big mess in the park. Barney creates a magical adventure where Mel learns it's important to clean up and care for a place that's special to you and your community.

added.title: One Ripe Tomato
added.description: When Vivie disagrees with her friends about who gets to use a ripe garden tomato, Barney creates space for everyone to share their ideas. Vivie realizes it's important to share and they use the tomato to make a pizza everyone can enjoy.

added.title: Red Light Stop, Green Light Go
added.description: Mel keeps trying to do a cool scooter trick and doesn't want to rest until she gets it right, but Mel pushes her body too far. Barney and Billy help Mel learn to listen to what her body is feeling and why it's important to do so.

added.title: Big, Bigger, Best
added.description: David feels like he's too small to do the all things his big brother can do, so Barney makes him super-sized. But throughout his super-sized adventures David realizes the importance of loving himself just as he is.

added.title: Practice Makes Purple
added.description: When Vivie discovers she's not amazing at soccer the first time she tries, she thinks she'll never be good at it. Barney creates fantastiical practice drills to help Vivie learn how practice can help her get better.

added.title: Team Mateys
added.description: When Mel's pretzel is eaten by a pigeon, Barney creates a high-seas adventure to find another, but it goes awry when Captain Mel doesn't listen to her crew. Mel realizes it's important to listen to others when you're working as a team.

added.title: The Easter Bunnies
added.description: The Easter Bunny is sick, so she hires The Looney Builders to take over the festivities and ensure Looneyburg has a great Easter.

added.title: Junior
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Ma and Pa Bear to build a bedroom for their son, Junior, whose excitement causes setbacks.

added.title: Looney Moon
added.description: When The Looney Builders help Wile E. Coyote build a telescope to view the Looney Moon, Tweety must face his fear of the dark.

added.title: Glamp Out
added.description: Gossamer invites The Looney Builders on a camping trip. They plan to build a simple campsite until Daffy insists they go "glamping" instead.

added.title: Outer Space
added.description: The Looney Builders build Marvin the Martian and his Martian crew a space station. Marvin soon becomes overwhelmed by his Martian crew's antics and lack of personal space.

added.title: That Dizzy Feeling
added.description: Vivie and Barney roll down the hill, again and again. When Vivie feels dizzy, she reveals that she's nervous to speak up about it because she doesn't want to ruin the fun. Barney thanks Vivie for being honest and they pick another game to play!

added.title: Make It Myself
added.description: When Vivie's newly-built sandcastle is accidentally destroyed, Barney offers to help her rebuild it using a little magic, but Vivie wants to do it all by herself. Together, they enjoy the process of constructing a new sandcastle from scratch.

added.title: A Big Sad
added.description: After Vivie reads a sad story with her Nonna, Barney helps her embrace that it's okay to be sad sometimes. After feeling OK sitting in her sadness for a bit, Vivie comes up with a happy ending for the story.

added.title: Billy's Intro
added.description: Billy takes us on a tour all around the park while riding his scooter! Follow along as he shows off some of his coolest moves.

added.title: Sharing
added.description: Mel is upset that Vivie and Baby Bop won't share the swings with her. Barney encourages Mel to sing about her frustration -- but when Barney asks Mel to share her microphone, Mel realizes that it's okay to wait to share until you're ready.

added.title: Here if You Need Me
added.description: Mel tries to swing all the way across the monkey bars without any help. Barney lets Mel know he's there just in case she needs him. After a few tries, Mel makes it, and lets Barney know that it was because she knew he was there that she could do it.

added.title: Anger
added.description: Mel gets angry after accidentally crashing her toy plane into a tree. Barney helps Mel find healthy ways to express her anger and calm down -- and together, they fix her plane.

added.title: Check in on Your Body
added.description: When David asks Barney to play, Barney accidentally forgets to listen to his body and plays straight through his daily nap! He feels very sleepy and David helps Barney check in on his body. After a brief snooze Barney is ready to play again!

added.title: Little by Little
added.description: David gets scared to go down the high slide. Barney comforts David and shows him how to take it step by step until he feels ready to try the slide.
